<br>
Over the last few weeks, a few moderators and members have been working together to define the new content areas for the bbarden network, with a view to producing some articles for the web site.  Between the team, we have spent many hours refining the specifics of our ideas.  This brainstorming is extremely valuable to ensure that we are producing the best possible results from the team.<br>
<br>
The current team members and their respective roles are as follows:<br>
<br>
bbarden - Lead Editor &amp; Designer<br>
ToTaL - Tech Editor<br>
Leuqarte - Tech Assistant<br>
Dash - Debates Editor<br>
Confound - Debates Assistant<br>
Candy Kiddie - Promotions Editor<br>
Kirbz - Gaming Editor<br>
Silva - Profile Editor<br>
Starry - Profile Assistant<br>
<br>
We also have a number of contributors who are involved in our discussions, but not &quot;officially&quot; on the team at the moment.<br>
<br>
In basic terms, each of the editors will be responsible for producing some of the web site content, with the assistants playing a key part.  When I say &quot;producing&quot; content, it will not be written purely by the editors. (The exception to this is the Promotions Editor, whose primary role is to spread the word about the network, and generate new interest.)  The editors will source content from the forums and from contributors - which can be anyone.  You may be approached by a member of the team if we think you can help us out!<br>
<br>
As things progress we will be making additional announcements to keep you updated.  We don't want to give away too much just yet, as we want to make sure we get it right before announcing anything else.  That said, if you have any comments please let me know.<br>
<br>
Cheers<br>
